<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="278" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1207,2024]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1387,1412]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin adjective that refers to the remoteness (about 
<quantity box="[1198,1286,1387,1412]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="278" unit="km" value="650.0">650 km</quantity>
) between the two known populations of this species (
<collectingRegion box="[594,700,1423,1448]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[754,977,1423,1448]" country="Argentina" name="Santiago del Estero" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">
<collectingRegion box="[754,852,1423,1448]" country="Chile" name="Region Metropolitana" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Santiago</collectingRegion>
del Estero
</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="278" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1207,2024]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1459,1484]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grismado &amp; Carrión, 2017" authorityName="Grismado &amp; Carrión" authorityYear="2017" box="[473,582,1460,1483]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Almafuerte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="remota" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[473,582,1460,1483]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">A. remota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[590,680,1459,1484]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[590,680,1459,1484]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grismado &amp; Carrión, 2017" authorityName="Grismado &amp; Carrión" authorityYear="2017" box="[926,1059,1459,1484]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Almafuerte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[926,1059,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">A. goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1067,1157,1459,1484]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1067,1157,1459,1484]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the relative sizes and proportions of the embolus and conductor, but differs by the shortened, more dorsally oriented RTA, the larger and curved backwards RTP, and by lacking the conspicuous ventral tegular protrusion (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1234,1531,1556]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[239,1348,193,1746]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[239,1348,193,1746]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Almafuerte remota sp. nov., male holotype. a, habitus dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, left palp, prolateral view; d, same, retrolateral view, e, same, detail of RTA; f, left palp, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036139/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Figs. 14 c–f</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1247,1328,1531,1556]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[154,1415,377,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 17. Almafuerte spp., genitalia. a – e, Almafuerte remota, sp. nov.; a – b, male holotype, a, left palp ventral view; b, same retrolateral view; c – e, internal genitalia of three females, cleared, dorsal view. c, d, Colonia Dora (paratypes MACN-Ar 35566, preparations CJG- 1522 and 1523 respectively), e, Santa Catalina (MACN-Ar 35652); f, Almafuerte kuru, sp. nov., paratype female (MACN-Ar 36687), internal genitalia, cleared, dorsal view. Scale bars: a – e = 0.2; f = 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036145/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">17 a–b</figureCitation>
); females are easily recognized by the C-shaped semicircular atria at sides of the epigynum, in where the copulatory openings are located (
<figureCitation box="[288,429,1603,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1634,1656]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1613]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,337,1613]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 15. Almafuerte remota sp. nov., a – b, e, female from Colonia Dora (paratype MACN-Ar 35558); c – d, g, female from Álvarez Condarco (paratype MACN-Ar 36724) f, female from Santa Catalina (MACN-Ar 35652); a, c, habitus dorsal view; b, d, same, ventral view; e – g, epigyna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036141/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Figs. 15 e–g</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[441,518,1603,1627]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[154,1415,377,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 17. Almafuerte spp., genitalia. a – e, Almafuerte remota, sp. nov.; a – b, male holotype, a, left palp ventral view; b, same retrolateral view; c – e, internal genitalia of three females, cleared, dorsal view. c, d, Colonia Dora (paratypes MACN-Ar 35566, preparations CJG- 1522 and 1523 respectively), e, Santa Catalina (MACN-Ar 35652); f, Almafuerte kuru, sp. nov., paratype female (MACN-Ar 36687), internal genitalia, cleared, dorsal view. Scale bars: a – e = 0.2; f = 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036145/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">17 c–e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="15" pageNumber="278" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1207,2024]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1639,1664]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[353,517,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">
Male 
<typeStatus box="[420,517,1639,1664]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: Measurements: Total length 7.63, carapace 3.42 long, 2.62 wide; sternum 1.89 long, 1.46 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.147, ALE 0.151, PME 0.166, PLE 0.145; AME-AME 0.140, AME-ALE 0.030, PME-PME 0.056, PME-PLE 0.196, ALE-PLE 0.135. Legs (femur/patella/tibia/metatarsus/ tarsus); I 2.46/1.52/2.05/1.53/1.03, II 2.16/1.35/1.66/1.36/0.94, III 1.95/1.14/1.28/1.44/0.91, IV 2.54/1.37/1.99/ 2.04/1.04. Leg spination: femora: I d1-1, pd0-0-0/1-1; II d1-1, pd 0-1-1-1; III d1-1, pd0-1-1, rd0-1-1; IV d1-1, p0- 1/0-0-1, r0-0-0-1(left) 0-0-0-0-2 (right); patellae: III r1, IV r1; tibiae: I 
<date box="[966,1019,1819,1843]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
-2ap, p1-0-0 (left) p0-1-0-1(right); II 
<date box="[151,203,1855,1879]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
-2ap, p1-0-1- 
<date box="[347,392,1855,1879]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">1III</date>
d1-0-0, p1-1-1, 
<date box="[575,626,1855,1879]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
-2ap (left) 2-2-2-2ap (right), r1-1; IV p1-1-1, 
<date box="[1135,1187,1855,1879]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
-2ap, r1-1 (left) r1-1-1 (right); metatarsi I 
<date box="[366,420,1891,1915]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
, p0-1-1, r0-0-1; II p0-1-1, 
<date box="[725,778,1891,1915]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
, r0-0-1; III d2-2/1, p1-1-1, 
<date box="[1091,1144,1891,1915]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
-2ap, r1-1-1; IV d0-2-0-2, p1/0-1-0-1, 
<date box="[284,338,1927,1951]" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">v2-2</date>
/1-2ap, r1-1-0-1. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[592,728,1927,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[239,1348,193,1746]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[239,1348,193,1746]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Almafuerte remota sp. nov., male holotype. a, habitus dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, left palp, prolateral view; d, same, retrolateral view, e, same, detail of RTA; f, left palp, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036139/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">Figs. 14 c–f</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[739,816,1927,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[154,1415,377,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 17. Almafuerte spp., genitalia. a – e, Almafuerte remota, sp. nov.; a – b, male holotype, a, left palp ventral view; b, same retrolateral view; c – e, internal genitalia of three females, cleared, dorsal view. c, d, Colonia Dora (paratypes MACN-Ar 35566, preparations CJG- 1522 and 1523 respectively), e, Santa Catalina (MACN-Ar 35652); f, Almafuerte kuru, sp. nov., paratype female (MACN-Ar 36687), internal genitalia, cleared, dorsal view. Scale bars: a – e = 0.2; f = 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036145/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="278">17 a, b</figureCitation>
): RTA dorsally displaced, with both branches relatively short, RTP large, backwardly curved, conductor with wide base, slightly curved at its end. All other characters are common for the genus.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1036139/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="279" targetBox="[239,1348,193,1746]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1768,1820]" pageId="16" pageNumber="279">
